  "description": [
    "Flathead Indian Customs My home is on the Flathead Reservation All the Flathead Indians belong to the Catholic religion There are churches in nearly every town But about the centre of the reservation theres a town called St Ignatius Mission Theres a nice big church there the biggest church in the state of Montana There are three big Catholic schools and on Christmas Easter Sunday or any other big day the people from all over the reservation go to church there When a person dies the closest relative makes a feast They kill a cow and cook the meat and they also buy lots of things from the stores After they have the feast ready all the people around that com munity go to that feast and the chiefs give good speeches about God Then they pray in their own language and sing After they are through praying some of the squaws pass the food around to each family They have a big tent and the men eat inside the tent and the women on the outside After they are through eating the chief gets up and gives a sorrowful speech about the dead person Pretty near ly all the"
  ],
